#=USAGE=
#== MAIN PARSE SCRIPT PARAMETERS
# cloudify -h                                                           Print this usage help
#
# cloudify environment|env init                                         Initialize cloudify before use (required once per session)
# cloudify packages|pkg ls  --select [pkg...]                           List package(s) (1)
# cloudify packages|pkg ls  --select [#hashtag...] [@tag...]            List packages filtered by hashtags and tags (1)(2)
#                                                                       Packages must have ALL listed hastags and tags
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (2)
# cloudify packages|pkg ls  --select [@tag...]                          List packages filtered by tags that are compatible with runtime platform (4)
#                                                                       Packages must have ALL listed tags.
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (2)
# cloudify packages|pkg ls  --select @all                               List all packages compatibles with runtime platform (4)
# cloudify packages|pkg add --select [pkg...]                           Install package(s) on local machine
#                                                                       Installation of packages is done in the order of appearance (3)
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (2)
# cloudify packages|pkg add --select [@tag...]                          Install packages filtered by tags that are compatible with runtime platform (4)
#                                                                       Packages must have ALL listed tags.
#                                                                       Installation of package is done in the order of appearance (3)
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (2)
# cloudify packages|pkg add --select @default                           Install packages tagged '@default' that are compatible with runtime platform (4)
#                                                                       Installation of package is done in the order of appearance (3)
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (2)
# cloudify packages|pkg add --select ... --on [host...]                 Add selected packages on host(s)
#                                                                       Selected hosts must be alive
# cloudify packages|pkg add --select ... --on [@tag...]                 Add selected packages on inventory hosts filtered by tags
#                                                                       Hosts must have ALL listed tags and be alive
#                                                                       '--on' options can be repeated (5)
# cloudify hosts|hst ls  --select [host...]                             List inventory host(s) (1)
# cloudify hosts|hst ls  --select [@tag...]                             List inventory hosts filtered by tags
#                                                                       Hosts must have ALL listed tags.
#                                                                       '--select' options can be repeated (3)
# cloudify hosts|hst ls  --select @all                                  List all inventory hosts
# cloudify hosts|hst ls [--select [...]] --state alive|stopped|dead     List inventory hosts that are alive|stopped|dead
# cloudify hosts|hst shell host                                         Open a shell session on host
# cloudify hostnames|hsn add host [IP]                                   Add IP/host in local /etc/hosts
#                                                                       If IP isn't specified, cloudify tries to discover it (6)
# cloudify credentials|crd add user [localhost|host|github|gitlab]      Interactively set user credentials of host, github, gitlab
#                                                                       Defaults to localhost
# cloudify credentials|crd remove user [localhost|host|github|gitlab]   Interactively unset user credentials of host, github, gitlab
#                                                                       Defaults to localhost
#
# cloudify test|tst                                                     Development helper to test code
#
# Usage footnotes:
# (1)   Print EXISTING packages/hosts. In future version, may also print informations related to listed packages/hosts
# (2)   Inside a '--select' clause, a 'AND' logical operator is applied to conditions.  Between successive '--select' clauses a 'OR' logical operator is applied.
# (3)   Order of appearance follows not-so-simple rules:
#           - A package depended package always come before its dependent packages
#           - Packages selected with a '--select' clause always come before packages selected by subsequent '--select' clause
#           - Inside a '--select' clause, packages selected by name comes in the order they're named.
#           - Inside a '--select' clause, packages selected by a tag|hashtag always come before packages selected by subsequent tags|hashtags
#           - Inside a '--select' clause, packages selected by the same tag|hashtag come in alphabetic order of packag names.
# (4)   The runtime platform is runtime environement of the host on which current instance of cloudify is running (Cloudify calls itself recursively on different hosts)
#       The runtime environment can defined by OS, OS/distro or OS/distro/distro_version
#       Current version of cloudify will only check that packages are compatible with the OS and Distro
#       In the future:
#           - Each package will have a .manifest.yml file describing supported OSs, distros and distro versions ranges
#           - Each inventory host will have a .status.yml file containing its OS, distro and distro version
#       With these, cloudify will be much smarter in assessing package/host compatibility
# (5)   Inside a '--on' clause, actions (run|kill|add|exec) are performed in parallel on specified hosts
#       hosts designated by an '--on' clause are always processed before hosts designated by a subsequent '--on' clause
# (6)   IP is retrieved from the following source (in this order)
#           - /etc/localhost (of runtime host)
#           - LXD server
#           - DNS

